Baby-sitting is an arcane art. It has nothing to do with babies sitting anywhere.
Babies cannot take care of themselves. That started as a rumour. And then fueled the growth of an industry. Baby-sitting.
Babies are high on idividualism, versatility and willpower. Qualities that most average adults lack. Left to themselves, babies swallow marbles (when not shoving them up their nostrils), eat mud, crawl into places they cant crawl out of, and generally leave their mark (mostly smelly) everywhere. The whole idea of baby-sitting is to curb a baby from such free expression. To bring it to the level of adult mediocrity. To make it conform to stodgy insipidness.
Free the babies. Stand against baby-sitting